Problem: There are 15 trees in the grove.content:
The cost of the paint is proportional to their surface area while the cost of the concrete is proportional to their volume. Let the proportionality constants for paint and concrete be $p$ and $c$, respectively. Then we can set up two equations:
\begin{align*}
p(6-1) &= 6.80-1.30 = 5.50 \\
p(12-4) &= c(24-8)
\end{align*}
Simplifying, we get $5p=5.50$ and $8p=16c$. Solving for $p$ in the first equation, we get $p=1.10$. Substituting into the second equation, we get $8(1.10)=16c$, so $c=0.55$. 

Now we can find the cost of a 3 inch cube:
\begin{align*}
\text{Cost} &= p(54) + c(27) \\
&= 1.10(54) + 0.55(27) \\
&= 59.40
\end{align*}
Therefore, a 3 inch cube would cost $\$59.40$ to make. The answer is $\boxed{59.40}$.

Problem: There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the grove today. After they are done, there will be 21 trees. How many trees did the grove workers plant today?
Answer: There are 15 trees originally. Then there were 21 trees after the Grove workers planted some more. So there must have been 21 - 15 = 6 trees that were planted. The answer is 6.
